<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Activate Prim Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Activates nearby prim-based objects, most commonly gates/doors and electric fences.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Activate Prim Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Activate Prim</Bold> Event Point activates a nearby prim/object when the Event
        Point is triggered. In normal mission editing, its most practical and common use is opening
        <Bold>Gate</Bold> buildings.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Gates are shown in blue in the Map Editor and Mission Editor. To open one, place the Activate
        Prim Event Point close to the gate, set the prim type to <Bold>Door</Bold>, and trigger the
        Event Point through mission logic. When the Event Point fires, the nearest matching gate opens
        roughly <Bold>90 degrees</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Practical summary:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Place Activate Prim near the object to activate. For gates, choose Door.
                    When triggered, the nearest gate opens.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Placement matters:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Activate Prim works by proximity. Place it close to the intended gate, fence, or prim.
                    If it is closer to the wrong object, the wrong object may be activated, or nothing useful may happen.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding an Activate Prim Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To add one, click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel, select
        <Bold>Activate Prim</Bold> from the Event Point type list, and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The <Bold>Edit EventPoint</Bold> window opens with the common properties, trigger settings,
        listening mode, and the Activate Prim-specific <Bold>Prim Type</Bold> field.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_add_type.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Activate Prim uses the standard Event Point common properties: index number, Event Point
        type, letter group, colour, position, trigger settings, and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The most important common property is <Bold>position</Bold>. The Event Point should be placed
        close to the prim/object you want to activate.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Position
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold> to place the Event Point close to the gate, fence, or
        other prim you want to activate.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        For gate-opening logic, place the Event Point directly on or very near the blue gate marker.
        For electric fence logic, place it near the fence section that should become electrified.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_position_near_gate.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Prim Type
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Activate Prim has one type-specific setting: <Bold>Prim Type</Bold>. This tells the game what
        kind of nearby prim/object should be activated.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_type_dropdown.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        The available options are:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Door</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Electric Fence</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Security Cam</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Anim Prim</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Of these, the two practical options currently in use are <Bold>Door</Bold> and
        <Bold>Electric Fence</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Door
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Door</Bold> when activating a gate. Place the Activate Prim Event Point close to
        the gate. When triggered, the nearest gate opens approximately 90 degrees. This is the most
        common use of Activate Prim.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Electric Fence
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Electric Fence</Bold> when activating an electric fence. Place the Event Point close
        to the relevant fence section. When triggered, the fence becomes electrified and shocks the
        player if touched.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Security Cam
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        This option exists, but it is not commonly used in current mission workflows. Treat it as
        uncertain unless deliberately testing security-camera-related prim activation.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Anim Prim
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        This option exists, but it is not commonly used in current mission workflows. It may relate
        to activating an animated prim/object, but should be treated as uncertain unless tested in
        the specific mission scenario.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Common Setup: Switch Opens Gate
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The most common Activate Prim setup is a switch that opens a gate. In this setup, the player
        uses a switch prim, a <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold> detects the player’s use action, and the
        Activate Prim Event Point opens the gate through a dependency trigger.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_gate_switch_setup.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Event Point Chain
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The typical chain is:
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">
Player uses switch -&gt; Simple Waypoint triggers -&gt; Activate Prim dependency fires -&gt; Gate opens
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        The player does not usually trigger the Activate Prim Event Point directly. Instead, the
        player triggers a nearby Simple Waypoint by pressing use near the switch. The Activate Prim
        Event Point then depends on that Simple Waypoint.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Step 1: Create the Switch Trigger Simple Waypoint
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        First, create a <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold> Event Point and place it on top of or very close
        to the switch prim object.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> Player Uses in Radius.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> None.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Radius:</Bold> small value, for example <Bold>128</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Position:</Bold> directly on or near the switch prim.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The Simple Waypoint acts as the trigger guard for the switch. When the player uses the switch
        while inside the radius, the Simple Waypoint activates.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_simple_waypoint_switch.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Radius tip:</Run>
                <Run>
                    A radius around 128 is a good starting value for a switch-use trigger. Adjust it if the player needs to stand too precisely or can trigger it from too far away.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Step 2: Create the Activate Prim Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Next, create the <Bold>Activate Prim</Bold> Event Point and place it close to the gate.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Prim Type:</Bold> Door.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> Dependency.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> Active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Dependency EP:</Bold> the Event Point number of the Simple Waypoint placed on the switch.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Position:</Bold> close to the gate that should open.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The <Bold>Dependency EP</Bold> is the link between the switch trigger and the gate opening.
        When the Simple Waypoint activates, the Activate Prim Event Point’s dependency is satisfied,
        and the gate opens.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_dependency_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical Dependency EP detail:</Run>
                <Run>
                    The Activate Prim Event Point should reference the Simple Waypoint’s Event Point number in Dependency EP.
                    Do not put the gate’s number or the Activate Prim event’s own number there.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Other Trigger Setups
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The switch setup is the most common way to use Activate Prim, but it is not the only option.
        Activate Prim can be triggered by any suitable mission condition.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        For example, a gate could open when:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The player enters a radius.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>An NPC is arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A target is killed or arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A conversation finishes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A counter reaches a specific value.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A timer completes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Another objective or dependency is completed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Choose the trigger that matches the mission logic you want. The important part is that when
        the Activate Prim Event Point fires, it must be close enough to the intended prim/object and
        have the correct Prim Type selected.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Electric Fence Setup
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Activate Prim can also be used with <Bold>Electric Fence</Bold>. Place the Event Point close
        to the fence section and select <Bold>Electric Fence</Bold> as the Prim Type.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        When triggered, the nearest fence becomes electrified. A player who touches the electrified
        fence will be shocked.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_activate_prim_electric_fence.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This can be used for hazards, restricted areas, timed mission obstacles, or areas that become
        dangerous after a mission event.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Troubleshooting
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The gate does not open</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm Prim Type is set to <Bold>Door</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Activate Prim Event Point is close to the gate.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the gate is actually a gate/door object that can open.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Activate Prim trigger is firing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>If using Dependency, confirm Dependency EP points to the Simple Waypoint’s Event Point number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The switch does not trigger the gate</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Simple Waypoint is placed on or near the switch prim.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Simple Waypoint uses <Bold>Player Uses in Radius</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the radius is large enough, such as <Bold>128</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Activate Prim Event Point depends on the Simple Waypoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The wrong object activates</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Move the Activate Prim Event Point closer to the intended object.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check whether another compatible object is closer.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test after moving the Event Point to confirm the correct gate or fence is selected.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Gate Opening Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Identify the blue gate on the map.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create a <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold> on or near the switch prim.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the Simple Waypoint to <Bold>Triggered By: Player Uses in Radius</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the Simple Waypoint <Bold>Listening Mode</Bold> to <Bold>None</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the Simple Waypoint radius to a small value such as <Bold>128</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Note the Simple Waypoint’s Event Point number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create an <Bold>Activate Prim</Bold> Event Point close to the gate.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Prim Type</Bold> to <Bold>Door</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>Dependency</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Dependency EP</Bold> to the Simple Waypoint’s Event Point number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Listening Mode</Bold> to <Bold>Active</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final note:</Run>
                <Run>
                    The switch/dependency setup is common, but Activate Prim can be triggered by any mission condition.
                    The key requirements are correct Prim Type, correct placement, and a trigger that actually fires.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>
